" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Peritubular capillary hemodynamics",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 320px; height: 184px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Role of Starling's forces in the uptake of the reabsorbate by the peritubular capillary. Approximate values for the capillary hydraulic and oncotic pressures are included (in mmHg) and show a relatively large gradient favoring fluid movement into the capillary. The interstitial pressures are of lesser magnitude and tend to balance out, thereby making a smaller contribution to net fluid movement.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
